data.description: Welcome to this grand and spacious all-brick 5 bedroom, 3.5 bathroom home situated in Easley, SC, boasting an array of updated and refined features. The kitchen and den exhibit a small piece of history, featuring bricks from the original Easley Colony Theater (circa 1948), adding a touch of elegance and allure to the home. On arrival, the grand circular driveway leads you to a large covered front porch with columns, perfect for relaxing in rocking chairs. The front yard is adorned with majestic mature trees that add to the charm of the lot.  Upon entering the home, you'll be greeted by a spacious foyer that leads to a formal dining room and living room. Continuing on, the oversized den with a gas fireplace promises a comfortable space for family time. A chef-worthy kitchen with a built-in brick oven or coffee bar and walk-in butlers pantry awaits in the same wing of the home, accompanied by a full laundry room, a guest half bath, and an office space separated from the living quarters.  The other wing of the home features four spacious bedrooms, including two owner's suites, making it ideal for multi-generational living. The primary owner's suite boasts a sitting room, dual walk-in closets, a jetted tub, a separate walk-in shower, dual vanity, and a private entrance onto a private deck with a gazebo. The back of the home features a large screened-in porch overlooking 1.69 acres of mature hardwood trees, providing additional privacy around the property. The home offers ample parking outside the large driveway, with an attached 2-car garage and a detached 1-car garage and workshop at the back. Recent updates include a new roof, HVAC, ductwork, flooring, and paint all less than two years old with regularly scheduled maintenance on the heating and air and plumbing.
